column37: Won soft-ground Bangor bumper on rules debut a year ago and probably bettered that performance when close second of 13 under penalty at Southwell (good) last December; can win over hurdles soon but Storming George had stronger bumper form and appeals more.

column37: Won 16-runner Doncaster bumper (good to soft) on debut in January and was creditable fifth of 15 in Grade 2 Aintree bumper (good) in April; should have a good future over jumps; commands respect.

column4: Greene King Novices' Handicap Chase (GBB Race)

column36: Course winner over hurdles when fresh last autumn; respected on chasing debut
column37: Front-runner who returned from break with two hurdle wins (one here) last autumn and was a respectable fourth in fairly valuable handicap here (2m, good to soft) on latest outing in March; could be hard to catch if he gets into a good jumping rhythm on this chasing debut.

column4: Greene King Novices' Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 15/8 A Pai De Nom, 100/30 Gentleman Toboot, 5/1 Tommy Pickles, 6/1 Noahsgreatrainbow, 13/2 Alidam, 12/1 Thankyouandplease, 14/1 Border Gem, 33/1 Pougie
column36: Triple chase winner in spring; made low-key return this month; this race is easier
column37: Progressive over fences in the spring, winning three times on good ground (2m-2m1f); retuned from break with low-key run at Kempton this month but this race is easier and he may still have more improvement to come.

column4: Greene King Novices' Handicap Chase (GBB Race)

column37: Won three-runner mares' chase pretty comfortably over C&D (good) 12 days ago and is now 2-3 over fences; 8lb higher today but reunited with 7lb claimer Benjamin Macey (aboard for first win); obvious contender.

column4: Greene King Novices' Handicap Chase (GBB Race)
column20: 15/8 A Pai De Nom, 100/30 Gentleman Toboot, 5/1 Tommy Pickles, 6/1 Noahsgreatrainbow, 13/2 Alidam, 12/1 Thankyouandplease, 14/1 Border Gem, 33/1 Pougie
column36: Gave good account when second of four over C&D in June; back from five-month break
column37: 0-14 under all codes; gave good account when second of four over C&D (good) in June and remains unexposed over fences but today's race is stronger and he has fitness to prove after five-month break.

column4: Greene King Fillies' Juvenile Hurdle (GBB Race)

column36: Won at Newton Abbot in August and made the frame on other five hurdling starts; big player
column37: Keen-going front-runner who has made the frame on all six hurdling starts, most notably when winning by 8l at Newton Abbot (2m1f, good) in August; has her limitations but can cope if the ground is good to soft here (untested on anything slower) and ought to make another bold bid.

column4: Greene King Fillies' Juvenile Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/10 Manyana Blue, 13/8 Zahra Dodville, 4/1 Mystical Mabel, 40/1 Jazz Talking, 50/1 Madame Pomone
column36: Unplaced all six Flat starts; makes limited appeal on hurdling debut
column37: Unplaced all six Flat starts (1m-1m4f), most recently when well down the field in low-grade AW handicap this month; sports refitted hood for this hurdling debut; tongue-tie removed; makes limited appeal.

column4: Greene King Fillies' Juvenile Hurdle (GBB Race)
column20: 11/10 Manyana Blue, 13/8 Zahra Dodville, 4/1 Mystical Mabel, 40/1 Jazz Talking, 50/1 Madame Pomone
column36: Well beaten when 40-1 for debut at Ludlow (2m, good to firm) three weeks ago
column37: Out of a French hurdle winner; well beaten when 40-1 for debut at Ludlow (2m, good to firm) three weeks ago; remains best watched.

column4: Greene King Fillies' Juvenile Hurdle (GBB Race)

column36: Running well before jumping erratically and falling at penultimate flight on hurdle debut
column37: Displayed promise on first two of her three Flat runs in June/July and was in process of running well before jumping erratically and falling at penultimate flight at Kempton (2m, good) ten days ago; comes with risk attached after that mishap but still enters calculations.

column4: Greene King Fillies' Juvenile Hurdle (GBB Race)

column36: Placed over hurdles in France; needs to be taken seriously on British debut
column37: Placed on hurdling debut at Fontainebleau (1m7f, very soft) in March and also showed clear promise (and a tendency to race too freely) on her other two starts in France; new trainer James Owen has booked Sean Bowen for this British debut; needs to be taken seriously.

column37: AW Flat winner but he's shown little over hurdles and was pulled up at Kempton (2m, good) on handicap debut in April; hard to make a case for back from a break; no cheekpieces today.

column36: Not yet fully exposed but needs to build on last month's encouraging Uttoxeter third.
column37: Was returning from a break and wind surgery when third at Uttoxeter (2m, good) last month; not yet fully exposed and has place claims if building on that.

column4: #Axe The Racing Tax Mares' Handicap Chase (Queen Boudicca Mares' Chase Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column36: Opened chase account at the 11th attempt; steps back in class and respected on return.
column37: Made all to open her chase account when exploiting a handy mark in four-runner race at Wincanton (3m1f, good) in March; safely held in stronger company at Cheltenham the following month but this is more her level, and she's respected back from a break.

column4: #Axe The Racing Tax Mares' Handicap Chase (Queen Boudicca Mares' Chase Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column36: Not ruled out on March's chase debut win but she's struggled to reach that level since.
column37: Won a Plumpton handicap (2m3.5f, good) on chase debut in March and may have found the follow-up bid coming too soon when second just four days later; however, she's struggled for form since and was beaten 31l on this month's C&D return.

column36: 2m5f hurdle winner who looks capable of better over fences if ready to go after a break.
column37: Justified support when winning over hurdles at Hereford (2m5f, good to soft) in February off 5lb lower; returns from a break for a belated switch to fences, but as a point winner she looks capable of better in this sphere.

column4: #Axe The Racing Tax Mares' Handicap Chase (Queen Boudicca Mares' Chase Qualifier) (GBB Race)
column36: Ran well for a long way on this month's return and could build on that back up in trip.
column37: 2-13 over fences, latest off 1lb higher in June 2024 under Sean Bowen; form has been mixed since but she ran well for a long way at Chepstow on return from nearly four months off; on a fair mark if building on that.

column4: #Axe The Racing Tax Mares' Handicap Chase (Queen Boudicca Mares' Chase Qualifier) (GBB Race)

column37: An easy C&D winner in May when ridden by Tabitha Worsley, but form has dipped badly since over fences and hurdles and was soundly beaten on this month's return from a break; has plenty to prove from out of the weights.
